PN,31901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FVictims of one of Britain's biggest
OL,8,Fscandals are to receive greater
OL,9,Fcompensation as the government
OL,10,Fincreases the amount available and
OL,11,Fmakes it easier for individuals to
OL,12,Fclaim.
OL,14,FOn Tuesday, the government announced
OL,15,Fit would make an additional #1 billion
OL,16,Favailable to those affected by the
OL,17,Finfected blood scandal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FThis additional funding comes on top
OL,8,Fof the #11.8 billion of funding for
OL,9,Fcompensation announced in the 2024
OL,10,Fautumn budget.
OL,12,FThe scandal saw people treated with
OL,13,Fcontaminated blood products between
OL,14,Fthe 1970s and 1990s, leading to
OL,15,Findividuals contracting diseases like
OL,16,FHepatitis and HIV.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FIt led to one of the UK's biggest
OL,8,Fpublic inquiries, with the
OL,9,Fcompensation scheme facing criticism
OL,10,Ffor its slow and, in some cases,
OL,11,Fseemingly low offers of compensation.
OL,13,FThis criticism prompted an additional
OL,14,Freport by the inquiry's chair, Sir
OL,15,FBrian Langstaff, in which he accused
OL,16,Fthe scheme of perpetuating further
OL,17,Fharm to the victims being left in the
OL,18,Fdark.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FAs of April 7, more than 3,200 offers
OL,8,Fof compensation have been made,
OL,9,Ftotalling over #2.6 billion. This is
OL,10,Fin addition to the #1.4 billion
OL,11,Falready paid out in interim payments.
OL,13,FAs well as increasing the amount of
OL,14,Fmoney allocated to the compensation
OL,15,Fscheme, the government will establish
OL,16,Fnew categories under which victims
OL,17,Fwill be eligible to apply for further
OL,18,Fcompensation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FThese will include awards for those
OL,8,Fwho suffered "psychological harm,"
OL,9,Fthose suffering side effects from
OL,10,F"interferon treatment", and those who
OL,11,Fwere prevented from entering a highly
OL,12,Fpaid career or disrupted their career
OL,13,Fprogression on account of their
OL,14,Finfection.
OL,16,FAnyone treated for a bleeding disorder
OL,17,Fwithin a specific time period will
OL,18,Falso receive an unethical research
OL,19,Faward at an increased value than what
OL,20,Fwas offered before.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FA 25% deduction applied to past care
OL,8,Fcompensation for people who choose to
OL,9,Freceive support scheme payments for
OL,10,Flife will also be removed.
OL,12,FThe government is also establishing a
OL,13,Fnew route for the community to raise
OL,14,Fconcerns with the Infected Blood
OL,15,FCompensation Scheme about its design
OL,16,For delivery.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FThis will include quarterly summaries
OL,8,Fof the feedback received and the
OL,9,Faction being taken as a result, aiming
OL,10,Fto increase the transparency of how
OL,11,Fthe community's concerns are dealt
OL,12,Fwith.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FAddressing MPs in the Commons,
OL,8,Fgovernment minister Nick Thomas-
OL,9,FSymonds said: "The community were
OL,10,Fclear that the scheme must do more to
OL,11,Frecognise people's individual
OL,12,Fexperiences and compensate them fairly
OL,13,Fin a way that minimises the
OL,14,Fadministrative burden placed upon
OL,15,Fthose who have been harmed, minimises
OL,16,Fthe demand for evidence and maintains
OL,17,Fthe delivery of tariff based
OL,18,Fcompensation, and those requirements
OL,19,Funderpin the changes.
OL,26,@qD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,F"While this government understands no
OL,8,Famount of money will make up for the
OL,9,Fsuffering endured by the infected
OL,10,Fblood community, I hope that these
OL,11,Fchanges to the compensation scheme
OL,12,Fdemonstrate our commitment in ensuring
OL,13,Fthis community receives the
OL,14,Fcompensation they rightly deserve."
OL,16,FMore than 30,000 people in the UK were
OL,17,Finfected with HIV and hepatitis C
OL,18,Fafter they were given contaminated
OL,19,Fblood and blood products between the
OL,20,F1970s and early 1990s.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FMore than 3,000 people have died as a
OL,8,Fresult, while survivors are living
OL,9,Fwith lifelong health implications.
OL,11,FThe Infected Blood Inquiry heard
OL,12,Fevidence over four years from hundreds
OL,13,Fof witnesses.
OL,15,FSince the Infected Blood Inquiry was
OL,16,Fannounced in July 2017, it is
OL,17,Festimated that 710 infected and
OL,18,Faffected people died by the time the
OL,19,Ffinal report was published in May 2024.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776243304
OL,3,CVictims of infected blood scandal to
OL,4,Creceive an extra #1 billion from
OL,5,Cgovernment
OL,7,FThe Inquiry's final report said the
OL,8,Fscandal "could largely have been
OL,9,Favoided" and there was a "pervasive"
OL,10,Fcover-up to hide the truth.
OL,12,FBoth government and health officials
OL,13,Fwere accused of "deception", including
OL,14,Fdestroying documents to "save face and
OL,15,Fsave expense".
OL,17,FA compensation scheme was announced
OL,18,Fthe day after the report was published.
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@HO]qD@ZOUqD@dO]uD@QOUuD@[O]vD@
OL,26,AYOUwD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
